## Group C ‚Äî Frontend Code Fixes ‚úÖ

### C1. Removed all `as any` Casts ‚Äî `useSettingsStore.ts`
- **File:** `src/store/useSettingsStore.ts` (full rewrite)
- All Supabase calls now use the properly typed client generated from `database.types.ts`
- `syncSettingsToDb` now passes a typed `user_settings` Insert object
- Empty catch blocks use `_e` (silent) with a comment instead of bare `{}`

### C2. Optimistic Update Rollback ‚Äî `useWeekStore.ts`
- **Functions fixed:** `toggleTaskComplete`, `createTask`, `updateTask`, `deleteTask`
- Each now snapshots `currentWeek` before mutation; on DB error, it reverts state and logs the error
- Prevents permanent UI/DB desync when a write fails silently

### C3. Replaced `alert()` with Inline Error Banner ‚Äî `Dashboard.tsx`
- Added `aiError` state
- Both `generateChallenge` and `fetchInsight` set this state on failure
- Error renders as a dismissible red banner at the top of the page ‚Äî non-blocking, styled

### C4. `BrowserRouter` Hoisted to App Root ‚Äî `App.tsx`
- `BrowserRouter` now wraps the entire app (above `AuthProvider`)
- Enables future public routes (password reset, invite links, landing page) without refactoring

### C5. Global `ErrorBoundary` ‚Äî `src/components/ErrorBoundary.tsx` (new file)
- Class component with `getDerivedStateFromError` + `componentDidCatch`
- Fallback renders a styled error UI with a collapsible error detail and a "Reload App" button
- Wraps `AuthProvider` + `AppRouter` in `App.tsx`

### C6. AI Keys Stripped from Weekly Report Export ‚Äî `useSettingsStore.ts`
- `exportWeeklyReport()` now destructures `aiKeys` out of state before serializing
- Downloaded JSON file no longer contains user's Gemini/Grok API keys

### C7. Week Number via `date-fns` ‚Äî `useWeekStore.ts`
- Installed `date-fns` package
- `getCurrentWeekInfo()` now uses `getISOWeek(now)` and `getISOWeekYear(now)`
- Eliminates the fragile manual calculation that could drift around year boundaries

